HEADWORD: Enchyma
<hw>En"chy*ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>'e`gchyma</grk> an infusion; <grk>'en</grk> in + <grk>chei^n</grk>
to pour.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The primitive formative juice,
from which the tissues, particularly the cellular tissue, are
formed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Encincture</ent>⟦br⟧
